.TH GIT-UNION 1 "March 2026" "git-union 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-union \- merge multiple git repositories into one monorepo
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git-union
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIMONO-DIR\fR \fIREPOS...\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBgit-union\fR creates a new git repository at \fIMONO-DIR\fR and replays commits
from each source repository into it.
.PP
Each source repository is placed under its own subdirectory:
.IP \(bu 2
\fIrepo\fR: subdirectory is the basename of \fIrepo\fR
.IP \(bu 2
\fIname=repo\fR: subdirectory is \fIname\fR
.PP
With \fB--sort\fR, commits are interleaved by author time while preserving
the original order of commits within each source repository.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-s, \-\-sort
Sort commits by author time while preserving per-repo order.
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-verbose
Enable verbose output.
.TP
.B \-q, \-\-quiet
Enable quiet output.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show help and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show version and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B git-union monodir foo bar
Create \fImonodir\fR and import repositories \fIfoo\fR and \fIbar\fR as
\fImonodir/foo\fR and \fImonodir/bar\fR.
.TP
.B git-union --sort mono core=../core ui=../frontend
Import named repositories and interleave commits by author time with ordering
constraints preserved per source repository.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 2
Invalid arguments or processing error.
